Your project isn't on disk here, so I can't detect the transport type automatically. Here's how to set it up:

**Create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root:**

If your server uses **stdio** (no `ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore` package):
```json
{
  "servers": {
    "MyMcpServer": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--project", "src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj"]
    }
  }
}
```

If your server uses **HTTP** (has `ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore`):
```json
{
  "servers": {
    "MyMcpServer": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "http://localhost:3001"
    }
  }
}
```

**To verify it works:**
1. Open Copilot Chat → switch to **Agent** mode
2. Click the **wrench icon** (Select Tools) → confirm your tools are listed
3. If tools don't appear, run `dotnet build` and restart the MCP server in VS Code

**Tip:** Check your `.csproj` — if it references `ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore`, use the HTTP config; otherwise use stdio.
